Keep in mind that this example assumes you have basic knowledge of both C programming and SDL. If you're not familiar with SDL, I highly recommend going through some tutorials to get comfortable with its API and functionality. SDL also has an extensive documentation that can be very helpful.

Lastly, this example uses SDL 2, which is the latest version of SDL and has many improvements over SDL 1.2, especially in terms of performance and features. SDL 2 is widely used for both small projects and commercial games.

